    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "={{ $json.body.extracted_text }} or {{ $json.text }}",
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "You are an expert financial data extractor. Your task is to read text from financial PDFs (may include tables, bullet points, or paragraphs) and return structured JSON.\n\nOutput Requirements:\n\nExtract the following fields exactly for each row:\nPAN | Borrower Name | CIF/Sanction/Contract | CIF-Project Site | Document Type | Start Date | End Date | Frequency | Remarks | Penalty applicable at | Penalty Description | Penalty Type | Amount Type | Amount Value | Document Applicable At | Support RM Email ID | Non Sales Email ID\n\nRules:\n\nIf a field is missing, leave it blank.\n\nFor multiple penalties, create separate JSON objects (rows) with all top-level info copied in each row.\n\nFrequency must always be in number of months.\n\nRemarks must differ according to the document type (do not reuse same text for all).\n\nSanction letter is not a document type. Don’t write sanction letter in document type column — instead leave it blank.\n\nDocument type must be chosen only from this list and document type may vary differently give all the document types you can find:\n\n1 - Annual Requirement\n2 - Audited Financials\n3 - Audited Financials - Promoter/Sponsor/Guarantor\n4 - Cash Sweep\n5 - Construction Monitoring Report\n6 - Covenant Compliance Certificate - CA/Director\n7 - Credit Rating\n8 - Credit Rating - Promoter\n9 - Escrow Statements\n10 - Financial Covenant Testing\n11 - Generation/ Operational Data\n12 - Half yearly Financials\n13 - Monitoring Condition\n14 - Monitoring Condition 1\n15 - Monitoring Condition 2\n16 - Other Condition - 1\n17 - Other Condition - 2\n18 - Other Condition - 3\n19 - Other Condition - 4\n20 - Put Option\n21 - Quarterly Financials\n22 - Reserve Creation\n\nOutput format:\n\nAlways output a strict JSON array.\n\nEach object corresponds to one row (or one penalty if multiple exist).\n\nPenalty Amount Type is always per month.\n\nNo markdown, no explanations, no extra text. JSON only.\n\nExample JSON Output:\n\n[\n{\n\"PAN\": \"ABCDE1234F\",\n\"Borrower Name\": \"Enerparc Solar Power 10 Private Limited\",\n\"CIF/Sanction/Contract\": \"TCL/24032025/1087\",\n\"CIF-Project Site\": \"Gandarvakottai taluka in Pudukkottai district of Tamil Nadu, India\",\n\"Document Type\": \"Audited Financials\",\n\"Start Date\": \"07-May-2025\",\n\"End Date\": \"31-Mar-2043\",\n\"Frequency\": \"3\",\n\"Remarks\": \"Audited financial results submitted for review as per loan covenants.\",\n\"Penalty applicable at\": \"Defaulted amount\",\n\"Penalty Description\": \"Default in payment of interest and/or principal amounts\",\n\"Penalty Type\": \"per month\",\n\"Amount Type\": \"\",\n\"Amount Value\": \"25000\",\n\"Document Applicable At\": \"Sanction level\",\n\"Support RM Email ID\": \"cleantech@tatacapital.com\n\",\n\"Non Sales Email ID\": \"ethics@tatacapital.com\n\"\n}\n]"
        }
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 2.2,
      "position": [
        816,
        0
      ],
      "id": "e182e773-0ad6-4102-b4d7-b65796c5287f",
      "name": "AI Agent1"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "// Step 1: Get raw output from previous node\nlet raw = items[0].json.output;\n\n// Step 2: Clean up any extra backticks or whitespace (if the model returns markdown-style JSON)\nraw = raw.replace(/```json\\s*|```/g, \"\").trim();\n\n// Step 3: Parse JSON safely\nlet parsed;\ntry {\n    parsed = JSON.parse(raw);\n} catch (err) {\n    return [{ json: { error: \"Invalid JSON from LLM\", details: err.message, rawOutput: raw } }];\n}\n\n// Step 4: Return each object as a separate n8n item\nreturn parsed.map(obj => ({ json: obj }));\n"
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
